records.addlTxt:
2:17 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Erik Johnson.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to count 1 as 5th offense with jail, fine, costs, revocation, IID, AODA and the balance of the counts will be dismissed.  State concurs.  Atty Johnson concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1, striking the alcohol fine enhancer.  Court orders all other counts be dismissed.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Johnson.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to: 

-180 days county jail, consecutive to any other sentence.  Court grants huber, out-of-county service and out-of-county travel.
-$600 fine plus court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.
-Blood Draw Fee - $42.50
-DL revocation - 24 months
-IID - 24 months
-AODA (GL)
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

-Sentence is to commence immediately.  Court remands the defendant to the custody of the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.

Court grants the defendant 3 days of sentence credit.

Court adjourned at 2:29 p.m.
